.SH ICON THEME STRUCTURE
Icon themes follow the freedesktop.org Icon Theme Specification:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
~/.local/share/icons/theme-name/
├── index.theme         (theme metadata and configuration)
├── 16x16/             (16×16 pixel icons)
│   ├── actions/
│   ├── apps/
│   ├── devices/
│   └── mimetypes/
├── 22x22/             (22×22 pixel icons)
├── 24x24/             (24×24 pixel icons)
├── 32x32/             (32×32 pixel icons)
├── 48x48/             (48×48 pixel icons)
└── scalable/          (SVG scalable icons)
.EE
.RE
.SH ICON CACHE
After installing or removing icon themes, the system icon cache should be updated:
.PP
.RS 4
# iconmgr automatically updates cache, but you can also run:
.br
iconmgr makecache
.br
# Or use system tools:
.br
gtk-update-icon-cache ~/.local/share/icons/theme-name
.br
gtk-update-icon-cache -f -t ~/.local/share/icons/theme-name
.RE
.PP
Desktop environments and applications may need to be restarted or refreshed to detect newly installed icon themes.
