.SH NOTES
.IP \(bu 2
Icon theme installations are managed through preconfigured GitHub repositories under the iconmgr organization
.IP \(bu 2
Each icon theme package includes SVG and PNG icon files at various sizes
.IP \(bu 2
Icon themes are installed to user directories by default (~/.local/share/icons)
.IP \(bu 2
System-wide installation may require root privileges
.IP \(bu 2
Icon cache is automatically updated after installation when using makecache
.IP \(bu 2
Installed icon themes are tracked in ~/.local/share/CasjaysDev/apps/iconmgr/
.IP \(bu 2
Desktop notifications can be disabled by setting ICONMGR_NOTIFY_ENABLED=no
.IP \(bu 2
Icon themes follow the freedesktop.org Icon Theme Specification
.IP \(bu 2
Most desktop environments require logout/login or restart to fully apply new icon themes
.IP \(bu 2
Some applications may require restart to detect newly installed icon themes
.SH ICON THEME INHERITANCE
Icon themes can inherit from other themes using the index.theme file:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
[Icon Theme]
Name=My Custom Theme
Inherits=Adwaita,hicolor
.EE
.RE
.PP
When an icon is not found in the current theme, the system checks inherited themes in order. The "hicolor" theme is the fallback theme and should always be present.
